name: Palimpsestus I
description: 2000x1500 pixels unique edition - Wiktionary definition: "From Latin palimpsēstus, from Ancient Greek παλίμψηστος (palímpsēstos, “scraped again”). A manuscript or document that has been erased or scraped clean, for reuse of the paper, parchment, vellum, or other medium on which it was written."     NOTE: Palimpsestus I is conceptually different from a décollage, although formally similar: a décollage is the deliberate outcome of a rersearch on artistic language and technique and actively pursued by the artist.
